title: chacha20
content:
# https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salsa20#ChaCha20_adoption

from Crypto.Util.number import long_to_bytes, bytes_to_long
import secrets

def ROTL(a, b):
    return (((a) << (b)) | ((a % 2**32) >> (32 - (b)))) % 2**32

def qr(x, a, b, c, d):
    x[a] += x[b]; x[d] ^= x[a]; x[d] = ROTL(x[d],16)
    x[c] += x[d]; x[b] ^= x[c]; x[b] = ROTL(x[b],12)
    x[a] += x[b]; x[d] ^= x[a]; x[d] = ROTL(x[d], 8)
    x[c] += x[d]; x[b] ^= x[c]; x[b] = ROTL(x[b], 7)

ROUNDS = 20

def chacha_block(inp):
    x = list(inp)
    for i in range(0, ROUNDS, 2):
        qr(x, 0, 4, 8, 12)
        qr(x, 1, 5, 9, 13)
        qr(x, 2, 6, 10, 14)
        qr(x, 3, 7, 11, 15)

        qr(x, 0, 5, 10, 15)
        qr(x, 1, 6, 11, 12)
        qr(x, 2, 7, 8, 13)
        qr(x, 3, 4, 9, 14)

    return [(a+b) % 2**32 for a, b in zip(x, inp)]

def chacha_init(key, nonce, counter):
    assert len(key) == 32
    assert len(nonce) == 8

    state = [0 for _ in range(16)]
    state[0] = bytes_to_long(b"expa"[::-1])
    state[1] = bytes_to_long(b"nd 3"[::-1])
    state[2] = bytes_to_long(b"2-by"[::-1])
    state[3] = bytes_to_long(b"te k"[::-1])

    key = bytes_to_long(key)
    nonce = bytes_to_long(nonce)

    for i in range(8):
        state[i+4] = key & 0xffffffff
        key >>= 32

    state[12] = (counter >> 32) & 0xffffffff
    state[13] = counter & 0xffffffff
    state[14] = (nonce >> 32) & 0xffffffff
    state[15] = nonce & 0xffffffff

    return state

state = chacha_init(secrets.token_bytes(32), secrets.token_bytes(8), 0)
buffer = b""
def encrypt(data):
    global state, buffer

    output = []
    for b in data:
        if len(buffer) == 0:
            buffer = b"".join(long_to_bytes(x).rjust(4, b"\x00") for x in state)
            state = chacha_block(state)
        output.append(b ^ buffer[0])
        buffer = buffer[1:]
    return bytes(output)

flag = b"fake_flag{FAKE_FLAG}"

if __name__ == "__main__":
    print("""This cipher is approved by Disk Jockey B.

1. Encrypt input
2. Encrypt flag
""")

    while True:
        inp = input("> ")

        match inp:
            case '1':
                print(encrypt(input("? ").encode()).hex())
            case '2':
                print(encrypt(flag).hex())
            case _:
                print("Bye!")
                exit()

title: SpinalHDL AXI crossbar with 2 SRAM's
Miner
content:
Modem = peripheral.find("modem") or error("No modem attached", 0)

Modem.open(80)

Event = nil
Finish = false

while not Finish do
    Event = { os.pullEvent("mining") }
    if Event[1] == "start" then
        Run()

    elseif Event[1] == "end" then
        Stop()

    elseif Event[1] == "info" then
        local info = GetInfo()
        Modem.transmit(40, 40, info)
    end
end

function Run()
    Modem.transmit(40, 40, "Running...")
end

function Stop()
    Finish = true
end

function GetInfo()
    return "I'm empty"
end

title: Simple mine
content:
local size = 16
for i=1,80,1 do
    for i=1,size,1 do
        for i=1,size-1,1 do
            turtle.dig()
            turtle.forward()
        end
        if (i~=size) then
            if (i%2 == 0) then
                turtle.turnLeft()
                turtle.dig()
                turtle.forward()
                turtle.turnLeft()
            else
                turtle.turnRight()
                turtle.dig()
                turtle.forward()
                turtle.turnRight()
            end
        end
    end
    
    turtle.turnRight()
    for i=1,size-1,1 do
        turtle.forward()
    end
    turtle.turnRight()
    turtle.digDown()
    turtle.down()
end

title: myconnection.py
content:
# mysqldb.py need this file
import logging
import time
import mysql.connector
# pip install mysql-connector-python

# Set up logger
logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
formatter = logging.Formatter("%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s")

# Log to console
handler = logging.StreamHandler()
handler.setFormatter(formatter)
logger.addHandler(handler)

# Also log to a file
file_handler = logging.FileHandler("cpy-errors.log")
file_handler.setFormatter(formatter)
logger.addHandler(file_handler) 

def connect_to_mysql(config, attempts=3, delay=2):
    attempt = 1
    # Implement a reconnection routine
    while attempt < attempts + 1:
        try:
            return mysql.connector.connect(**config)
        except (mysql.connector.Error, IOError) as err:
            if (attempts is attempt):
                # Attempts to reconnect failed; returning None
                logger.info("Failed to connect, exiting without a connection: %s", err)
                return None
            logger.info(
                "Connection failed: %s. Retrying (%d/%d)...",
                err,
                attempt,
                attempts-1,
            )
            # progressive reconnect delay
            time.sleep(delay ** attempt)
            attempt += 1
    return None

title: Manage TeaSpeak
content:
// To install
version=$(curl -s https://repo.teaspeak.de/server/linux/amd64_stable/latest)

# You need YASM (https://pastebin.com/BWTF8uxL)
# You need FFMepg (https://pastebin.com/2nj9d8NV)

# Create user
adduser --gecos --disabled-login --disabled-password ts

mkdir /home/ts
cd /home/ts
wget https://repo.teaspeak.de/server/linux/amd64_stable/TeaSpeak-$version.tar.gz
gunzip TeaSpeak-$version.tar.gz
tar xvf TeaSpeak-$version.tar
rm -r TeaSpeak-$version.tar
chmod -R 777 .
bash teastart_minimal.sh

chmod -R 777 .
sudo -u ts bash teastart.sh start

// To uninstall
cd /home/ts
sudo -u ts bash teastart.sh stop
deluser ts
rm -r /home/ts

tar xvf yasm-1.3.0.tar
mv yasm-1.3.0 /usr/local/yasm
rm -r yasm-1.3.0.tar
cd /usr/local/yasm
rm -r *.txt ABOUT-NLS AUTHORS ChangeLog INSTALL README
chmod -R 777 .
bash configure
make install

// To uninstall
rm -r /usr/local/share/man/man7 /usr/local/share/man/man1/yasm.1
rm -r /usr/local/include/*yasm*
rm -r /usr7bin/yasm

title: Manage FFmpeg
content:
// To install
mkdir /usr/local/ffmpeg
cd /usr/local/ffmpeg
git init
git pull https://github.com/FFmpeg/FFmpeg.git
rm -r .* *.md COPYING* CREDITS Changelog MAINTAINERS RELEASE
chmod -R 777 .
bash configure
make install
ln -s ffmpeg /usr/bin

// To uninstall
rm -r /usr/local/ffmpeg /usr/bin/ffmpeg

title: BWR - Changelog 05/01/24
content:
Soda Popper
~ Hype effect appears when at >15% hype
Better communicate to the user and enemy when air jumps are available on the scout.

Support Structures
~ Fixed health while constructing to be more consistent
Buildings were able to tank damage they shouldn't have while constructing, this fix should hopefully remedy that.

Sappers
+ Increased Spy Radar highlight time to 5 seconds (was 3s)
- This includes you too
A buff to its duration to allow for spy's team to followup a bit easier on him revealing the enemies, still counterbalanced by the spy risking exposing himself too.

Eyelander
+ Added, Press SPECIAL ATTACK to use 1 head to gain a 3 second speed boost
+ Removed max secondary ammo penalty
~ Audio and visual effect is played on using a head
- Heads capped at 6 max
- Speed boost effect removed on-kill
The weapon was considered fairly overkill with the instant speed boost it granted making it too easy to close the gap or escape after a kill. Rather than remove it outright, it was changed to be activated for the exchange of a head while also giving you a fairly low limit to them. This will hopefully keep that same utility and making it more flexible for the demo to use, but requiring he eat into his permanent buffs to benefit.

Persian Persuader
+ Added: +100% ammo gained from ammo packs
A way to lessen the downside of the weapon when used with either grenades or stickies, allowing the demo to stay topped off despite his lower max ammo amounts.

Mannmelter
+ Added +20% damage bonus
+ Removed: Mini-crits whenever it would crit
- Removed damage bonus vs burning targets
- Increased afterburn duration penalty to -60% (was -40%)
The prior version was rather convoluted in its expectations for you. This version attempts to be simpler to with a more punchier initial hit especially on a crit strike, with less need to setup on someone with afterburn.

title: garuda-lite-post-install
content:
#!/bin/bash

# Garuda Linux Post Install Script
# Automates installing common packages on Garuda Linux after a fresh install.
# Provides reusable functions to install packages, remove packages, and log operations.
# Customize the package lists below to suit your needs.

# Ensure the script has sudo privileges
if ! sudo true; then
  echo "Error: Script requires sudo privileges."
  exit 1
fi

# Colors for formatted output
RED='\033[0;31m'
GREEN='\033[0;32m'  
YELLOW='\033[1;33m'
CYAN='\033[0;36m'
ORANGE='\033[0;33m'
NC='\033[0m' # No Color

# Log file to store script execution details
LOG_FILE="installation_log.txt" 

# Create/clear log file
true > "$LOG_FILE"

# Log initialization
echo -e "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') - Initialization - Log file created: $LOG_FILE" >> "$LOG_FILE"

# Log function
log_message() {
  echo -e "$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') - $1" >> "$LOG_FILE" 
}

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message "Initialization"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

#--------------------------------------------------------

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message "Functions"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Check if package is installed
is_package_installed() {
  if pacman -Qi "$1" &>/dev/null; then
    return 0  # Package is installed
  else
    pacman -Si "$1"  # Print information about the package to help debug
    return 1  # Package is not installed
  fi
}

# Install a package
install_package() {
sudo pacman -S --noconfirm "$1" 2>&1 | tee -a "$LOG_FILE" >/dev/null

if sudo pacman -S --noconfirm "$1" 2>&1 | tee -a "$LOG_FILE" >/dev/null; then
    log_message "Installed $1 successfully."  
    echo -e "${GREEN}Installed $1 successfully.${NC}"
  else
    log_message "Failed to install $1."
    echo -e "${RED}Failed to install $1.${NC}"
    exit_with_error "Critical error: Package installation failed. Check $LOG_FILE for details."
  fi
}

# Remove a package
remove_package() {
sudo pacman -Rns --noconfirm "$1" 2>&1 | tee -a "$LOG_FILE" >/dev/null

if sudo pacman -Rns --noconfirm "$1"; then
    log_message "Removed $1 successfully."
    echo -e "${GREEN}Removed $1 successfully.${NC}"
  else
    log_message "Failed to remove $1." 
    echo -e "${RED}Failed to remove $1.${NC}"
    exit_with_error "Critical error: Package removal failed. Check $LOG_FILE for details."
  fi
}

# Check if command exists  
check_command() {
  command -v "$1" &>/dev/null
}

# Print error message and exit
exit_with_error() {
  log_message "Error: $1"
  echo -e "${RED}$1${NC}"
  exit 1
}

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Install Dependencies"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log installation dependencies
log_message "Checking and installing dependencies."

# Install git if not already installed  
if ! check_command "git"; then
  log_message "Installing git..."
  install_package "git" 
else
  log_message "Git already installed."
  echo -e "${YELLOW}Git already installed.${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
fi

# Install base-devel if missing
if ! is_package_installed "base-devel"; then
  log_message "Installing base-devel..."
  install_package "base-devel"
else
  log_message "Base-devel already installed."
  echo -e "${YELLOW}Base-devel already installed.${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"  
fi

# Install cargo-make if needed
if check_command "cargo-make"; then
  auto_install_cargo_make=false
  log_message "cargo-make already installed."
  echo -e "${YELLOW}cargo-make already installed.${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
fi

if [ "$auto_install_cargo_make" = true ]; then
  log_message "Installing cargo-make..."
  cargo install --force cargo-make --version 0.34.0
  log_message "cargo-make installed successfully."
  echo -e "${GREEN}cargo-make installed successfully.${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"  
fi

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Installing Packages"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

echo -e "\e[1;${ORANGE}\e[4mLIST OF PACKAGES TO INSTALL\e[0m"
echo  

# Log package installation
log_message "Installing packages."

# Get the directory where the script is located
SCRIPT_FOLDER="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)"

# List packages to install
mapfile -t packages_to_install <"$SCRIPT_FOLDER/packages/packages_to_install.txt"

# Debug output: Print the list of packages to install
echo "Packages to install: ${packages_to_install[@]}"

# Loop through packages to install
for package in "${packages_to_install[@]}"; do
  if ! is_package_installed "$package"; then
    log_message "Installing $package..."
    install_package "$package"
  else
    log_message "$package is already installed."
    echo -e "${YELLOW}$package is already installed.${NC}"
  fi  
done

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Vivaldi And Google Earth Pro Section"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Helper functions
create_directory() {
  mkdir -p "$1"
}

remove_if_exists() {
  rm -f "$1"
}

# Vivaldi paths
vivaldi_local_file="vivaldi.tar.gz"
vivaldi_remote_url="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/7fpk57lxgnj39ojagax4w/vivaldi.tar.gz?rlkey=mhehi0yh9t0cth1olw4sdb6ka&dl=0"
vivaldi_folder="$HOME/.config/vivaldi"

# Google Earth paths 
google_earth_local_file=".googleearth.tar.gz"
google_earth_remote_url="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/ufl2byrcco46tbni2kkf8/.googleearth.tar.gz?rlkey=bw1av820oi00jots1a7079om2&dl=0"
google_earth_folder="$HOME/.googleearth"

# Create Vivaldi directory
create_directory $vivaldi_folder

# Download and extract Vivaldi
log_message "Downloading Vivaldi..."
wget $vivaldi_remote_url -O $vivaldi_local_file
log_message "Extracting Vivaldi..."
tar xzf $vivaldi_local_file -C $vivaldi_folder --strip-components=1

# Create Google Earth directory 
create_directory $google_earth_folder

# Download and extract Google Earth
log_message "Downloading Google Earth..."
wget $google_earth_remote_url -O $google_earth_local_file
log_message "Extracting Google Earth..."
tar xzf $google_earth_local_file -C $google_earth_folder --strip-components=1

# Cleanup archives
log_message "Removing temporary files..."
remove_if_exists $vivaldi_local_file
remove_if_exists $google_earth_local_file

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Install espanso from AUR using Yay"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log espanso installation
log_message "Installing espanso from AUR."

install_espanso() {
  if ! command -v yay &>/dev/null; then
    exit_with_error "Error: 'Yay' is not installed. Please install it before running this script."
  fi

  echo -e "${CYAN}Installing espanso from AUR...${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
  yay -S --noconfirm espanso >> "$LOG_FILE" 2>&1

  if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
    echo -e "${GREEN}Espanso installed successfully.${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
    log_message "Espanso installed successfully."
  else
    log_message "Failed to install espanso. Check $LOG_FILE for details."
    exit_with_error "Error: Failed to install espanso. Check $LOG_FILE for details."
  fi
}

# Call the install_espanso function to handle install
install_espanso

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message "Install Hardcoded Fixer from AUR using Yay"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Attempt to install hardcode-fixer-git
if yay -S --noconfirm hardcode-fixer-git >> "$LOG_FILE" 2>&1; then
  log_message "Installation completed successfully"
else
  log_message "Failed to install hardcode-fixer-git from AUR. Check $LOG_FILE for details."
  handle_error "Failed to install hardcode-fixer-git from AUR."
fi

# Respond 'q' during the installation
echo -e "q\n" | yay -S --noconfirm hardcode-fixer-git >> "$LOG_FILE" 2>&1

# Check if the installation was successful
if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
  log_message "Installation completed successfully"
else
  log_message "Installation completed with errors. Check $LOG_FILE for details."
  handle_error "Installation completed with errors."
fi

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Removing Packages"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log package removal
log_message "Removing packages."  

# Get the directory where the script is located
SCRIPT_FOLDER="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)"

# List packages to uninstall
mapfile -t packages_to_uninstall <"$SCRIPT_FOLDER/packages/packages_to_remove.txt"

echo -e "\e[1;${ORANGE}\e[4mREMOVING PACKAGES\e[0m"
echo

# Debug output: Print the list of packages to uninstall
echo "Packages to uninstall: ${packages_to_uninstall[@]}"

for package in "${packages_to_uninstall[@]}"; do
  echo "Processing package: $package"

  if is_package_installed "$package"; then
    remove_package "$package"
  else
    log_message "$package is not installed."
    echo -e "${YELLOW}$package is not installed.${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
  fi
done

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Post-Installation Tasks"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

echo -e "\e[1;${ORANGE}\e[4mPOST-INSTALLATION TASKS\e[0m"
echo

# Log post-installation tasks
log_message "Performing post-installation tasks."

# Apply hblock rules to block ads, tracking, and malware domains
echo -e "${CYAN}Applying hblock rules to block ads, tracking, and malware domains...${NC}" | sudo tee -a "$LOG_FILE" >/dev/null
sudo hblock >> "$LOG_FILE" 2>&1

if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
  echo -e "${GREEN}hblock rules applied successfully.${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
  log_message "hblock rules applied successfully."  
else
  log_message "Failed to apply hblock rules."
  echo -e "${RED}Failed to apply hblock rules.${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
  exit_with_error "Critical error: hblock rules application failed. Check $LOG_FILE for details."
fi

# Register espanso service
espanso service register

# Start espanso after install
espanso start

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Start and Enable Firewalld"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Start the firewalld service to apply firewall rules
echo -e "${CYAN}Starting the firewalld service...${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE" 
echo | sudo systemctl start firewalld | sudo tee -a "$LOG_FILE" >/dev/null

# Enable the firewalld service
echo -e "${CYAN}Enabling the firewalld service...${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
echo | sudo systemctl enable firewalld | sudo tee -a "$LOG_FILE" >/dev/null

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Changing The Default Shell"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

chsh -s /usr/bin/fish

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Profile-Sync-Daemon (PSD) Operations"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log masking (disabling) the PSD service
log_message "Masking (disabling) the PSD service..."
echo -e "${CYAN}Masking (disabling) the PSD service...${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
systemctl --user mask psd >> "$LOG_FILE" 2>&1

if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
  echo -e "${GREEN}PSD service masked successfully.${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
else
  echo -e "${RED}Failed to mask PSD service.${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
  exit_with_error "Critical error: Failed to mask PSD service. Check $LOG_FILE for details."
fi

# Stop the PSD service  
log_message "Stopping the PSD service..."
echo -e "${CYAN}Stopping the PSD service...${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
systemctl --user stop psd >> "$LOG_FILE" 2>&1

if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
  echo -e "${GREEN}PSD service stopped successfully.${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE" 
else
  echo -e "${RED}Failed to stop PSD service.${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
  exit_with_error "Critical error: Failed to stop PSD service. Check $LOG_FILE for details."
fi

# Show the status of the psd (profile-sync-daemon) service
log_message "Showing the status of the PSD service..."
echo -e "${CYAN}Showing the status of the PSD service...${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
status_output=$(systemctl --user status psd 2>&1)

if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
  echo -e "${GREEN}PSD service status retrieved successfully.${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
  echo -e "${CYAN}${status_output}${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
else
  echo -e "${RED}Failed to retrieve PSD service status.${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
  echo -e "${CYAN}${status_output}${NC}" >> "$LOG_FILE"
  
  # Exit with an error only if the service is not masked
if [[ ! "$status_output" =~ "Unit psd.service is masked" ]]; then
    exit_with_error "Critical error: Failed to retrieve PSD service status. Check $LOG_FILE for details."
  fi
fi

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " SpotDL Configuration Operations"''
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log message for SpotDL
log_message "Starting SpotDL Config File Operations..."

# Specify the name of your predefined SpotDL config file (replace 'config.json' with your file name)
predefined_config_file="config.json"

# Path to the folder containing the script
SCRIPT_FOLDER="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)"

# Specify the directory path where you want to store the SpotDL config file
spotdl_config_dir="$HOME/.spotdl/"

# Function to copy SpotDL config file
copy_spotdl_config() {

  source_file="$1"
  destination_dir="$2"

  # Path to the config.json file within the script folder
  config_json_path="$SCRIPT_FOLDER/spotdl/$source_file"

  # Check if the source file exists
  if [ ! -f "$config_json_path" ]; then
    echo "Error: $config_json_path not found."
    exit 1
  fi

  # Create the directory if it doesn't exist
  mkdir -p "$destination_dir"

  # Copy the SpotDL config file
  echo -e "Copying $config_json_path to $destination_dir..."
  cp "$config_json_path" "$destination_dir/config.json"

  echo -e "Copied $config_json_path to $destination_dir successfully."
}

# Call the function to copy SpotDL config file
copy_spotdl_config "$predefined_config_file" "$spotdl_config_dir"

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Sublime Text 4 Configuration Operations"''
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Define variables
SOURCE_FOLDER="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)/sublime-text"
DESTINATION_FOLDER="$HOME/.config"

# Function to handle errors
handle_error() {
    log_message "Error: $1"
    exit 1
}

# Check if source folder exists
if [ ! -d "$SOURCE_FOLDER" ]; then
    handle_error "Source folder not found: $SOURCE_FOLDER"
fi

# Check if destination folder exists, create if not
if [ ! -d "$DESTINATION_FOLDER" ]; then
    mkdir -p "$DESTINATION_FOLDER" || handle_error "Failed to create destination folder: $DESTINATION_FOLDER"
fi

# Move Sublime Text 4 folder to .config
mv "$SOURCE_FOLDER" "$DESTINATION_FOLDER" || handle_error "Failed to move Sublime Text 4 folder"

# Log success message
log_message "Sublime Text 4 successfully moved to $DESTINATION_FOLDER"

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Dolphin Configuration Operations"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log message for Dolphin Configuration Operations
log_message "Starting Dolphin Configuration Operations..."

# Path to the folder containing the script
SCRIPT_FOLDER="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)"

# Path to the dolphinrc file within the script folder
DOLPHINRC_PATH="$SCRIPT_FOLDER/dolphin/dolphinrc" 

# Check if the dolphinrc file exists
if [ ! -f "$DOLPHINRC_PATH" ]; then
  log_message "Error: dolphinrc file not found in $SCRIPT_FOLDER/dolphin."
  exit 1
fi

# Create directories if they don't exist
USER_PLACES_DIR="$HOME/.local/share"
KXMLGUI5_DIR="$HOME/.local/share/kxmlgui5/dolphin"

mkdir -p "$USER_PLACES_DIR"
mkdir -p "$KXMLGUI5_DIR"

# Copy and replace the files from the correct location
USER_PLACES_FILE="$SCRIPT_FOLDER/dolphin/user-places.xbel"
KXMLGUI5_FILE="$KXMLGUI5_DIR/dolphinui.rc"

cp -f "$USER_PLACES_FILE" "$USER_PLACES_DIR"
cp -f "$SCRIPT_FOLDER/dolphin/dolphinui.rc" "$KXMLGUI5_FILE" 
cp -f "$DOLPHINRC_PATH" "$USER_PLACES_DIR/dolphinrc"

log_message "Copied user-places.xbel to $USER_PLACES_DIR"
log_message "Copied dolphinui.rc to $KXMLGUI5_FILE"
log_message "Copied dolphinrc to $USER_PLACES_DIR"

# Replace user's dolphinrc
USER_DOLPHINRC="$HOME/.config/dolphinrc"
cp "$DOLPHINRC_PATH" "$USER_DOLPHINRC"
log_message "Copied dolphinrc to $USER_DOLPHINRC"

# Replace root's dolphinrc using sudo  
ROOT_DOLPHINRC="/root/.config/dolphinrc"
sudo cp "$DOLPHINRC_PATH" "$ROOT_DOLPHINRC" 
log_message "Copied dolphinrc to $ROOT_DOLPHINRC with sudo"

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Neofetch Configuration Operations"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log message for Neofetch Configuration Operations
log_message "Starting Neofetch Configuration Operations..."

# Define source directory
SCRIPT_FOLDER="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)"

# Define source and destination paths
source_config="$SCRIPT_FOLDER/neofetch/config.conf"
destination_config="$HOME/.config/neofetch/config.conf" 

# Create neofetch config directory if needed
mkdir -p "$(dirname "$destination_config")"

# Check if destination file already exists
if [ ! -f "$destination_config" ]; then

  # Copy source config file
  cp "$source_config" "$destination_config"
  log_message "Neofetch configuration copied to $destination_config"

else

  # Skip copy if destination file already exists
  log_message "Neofetch configuration already exists at $destination_config"

fi

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Fish Configuration Operations"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log message for Fish Configuration Operations
log_message "Starting Fish Configuration Operations..."

# Get the directory where the script is located
SCRIPT_FOLDER="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)"

# Define the source path for the Fish shell configuration files
source_config="$SCRIPT_FOLDER/fish"

# Define the destination path for the Fish shell configuration directory
destination_config="$HOME/.config/fish"

# Create the destination directory if it doesn't exist
mkdir -p "$destination_config"

# Copy the configuration files to the destination directory
cp -rv "$source_config"/* "$destination_config"

# Print a message indicating successful setup
log_message "Fish shell configuration has been moved to: $destination_config"

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " GTK Configuration Operations"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log message for GTK Configuration Operations
log_message "Starting GTK Configuration Operations..."

# Get the directory where the script is located
SCRIPT_FOLDER="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)"

predefined_gtk_folders=("$SCRIPT_FOLDER/gtk/gtk-3.0" "$SCRIPT_FOLDER/gtk/gtk-4.0")
config_dir="/root/.config/"
log_file="$SCRIPT_FOLDER/your_log_file.log"

# Ensure the log file directory exists
log_dir=$(dirname "$log_file")
if [ ! -d "$log_dir" ]; then
  mkdir -p "$log_dir" 
fi

# Create the target directory if it doesn't exist  
if [ ! -d "$config_dir" ]; then
  sudo mkdir -p "$config_dir"
fi

# Move or copy the folders to /root/.config/ and log the operation
for gtk_folder in "${predefined_gtk_folders[@]}"; do
  if [ -d "$gtk_folder" ]; then
    sudo rsync -a "$gtk_folder" "$config_dir"

    # Retry removing the source directory until successful
    while ! sudo rm -r "$gtk_folder"; do
      sleep 1
    done

    log_message "Moved $gtk_folder to $config_dir"
  else
    log_message "Error: $gtk_folder not found."
  fi
done

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " KDE Service Menu Operations"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log message for KDE Service Menu Operations
log_message "Starting KDE Service Menu Operations..."

SCRIPT_DIR="$(dirname "$(readlink -f "$0")")"
DESTINATION_DIR="$HOME/.local/share/kservices5/ServiceMenus/"

mkdir -p "$DESTINATION_DIR"
cp "$SCRIPT_DIR/service-menus"/*.desktop "$DESTINATION_DIR"
log_message "Service menu files copied to: $DESTINATION_DIR"

log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"
log_message " Plasmoid Installation Operations"
log_message "--------------------------------------------------------"

# Log message for Plasmoid Installation Operations
log_message "Starting Plasmoid Installation Operations..."

SCRIPT_FOLDER="$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")"

# Function to install plasmoids
install_plasmoids() {
  plasmoids_file="$SCRIPT_FOLDER/packages/install_plasmoids.txt"
  downloads_dir="$HOME/Downloads"
  plasmoids_dir="$HOME/.local/share/plasma/plasmoids"

  mkdir -p "$plasmoids_dir"

  if [ -f "$plasmoids_file" ]; then
    mapfile -t plasmoid_git_repos < "$plasmoids_file"

    for git_repo in "${plasmoid_git_repos[@]}"; do
      log_message "Cloning $git_repo..."
      git clone "$git_repo" "$downloads_dir/$(basename "$git_repo" .git)" >> "$LOG_FILE" 2>&1
      plasmoid_name=$(basename "$git_repo" .git)
      cp -r "$downloads_dir/$plasmoid_name" "$plasmoids_dir" >> "$LOG_FILE" 2>&1
rm -rf "${downloads_dir:?}/$plasmoid_name" >> "$LOG_FILE" 2>&1
      log_message "Installed $plasmoid_name successfully."
    done
  else
    log_message "Error: $plasmoids_file not found."
  fi
}

install_plasmoids

log_message "SCRIPT EXECUTION COMPLETE"
echo

    "Samaya",
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------
local chat_box, me, sensor, counter, bridge, redstone
local euWorking, average, cb, me_a, s, bridgeCom, redstoneCom, allow_mem = true, false, false, false, false,
    false, false, false
-------------{OPTIONS}------------------
local redstoneSide = 4
local TIME_ZONE = 3
local widthBox = 90
local transBox = 0.2
local timeConstant = 0.5
local getY = 15
---------------------------------------------
local TC, RO, RN, RD, TPS = 2, 0, 0, 0, 0
local strTPS = ""
---------------------------------------------
local t_correction = TIME_ZONE * 3600
local chat_box_name = "¬ß8[¬ß4–ê–ª–∏—Å–∞¬ß8]"
local adm = "combomaster" -- –ù–∏–∫ –∞–¥–º–∏–Ω–∞ –∫–æ–º–ø–∞
local allow_mem = false -- –û—Ç–æ–±—Ä–∞–∂–∞—Ç—å –Ω–∞ —ç–∫—Ä–∞–Ω–µ –∫–æ–ª-–≤–æ –ø–∞–º—è—Ç–∏ –∏–ª–∏ –Ω–µ—Ç
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  local average_counter = {
  molecular = {
    proxy=component.proxy("d512140c-4397-43ea-9e63-bc8884fd838a"),
    icon="AdvancedSolarPanel:BlockMolecularTransformer",
    use=true,
    coordinates = {x = 1, y = getY + 75},
    color = colors.orange,
  },
  ractor = {
    proxy=component.proxy("990945ea-1742-4b5b-9c03-b2400cc4c741"),
    icon="dwcity:PalladiumReactorChamber",
    use=true,
    coordinates = {x = 1, y = getY + 55},
    color = colors.green,
  },
  solar = {
    proxy=component.proxy("0f93c660-c29b-4399-ba6a-72a8584a6a95"),
    icon="AdvancedSolarPanel:BlockAdvSolarPanel",
    use=true,
    coordinates = {x = 1, y = getY + 35},
    color = colors.blue,
  }  
}

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------    
local localize = {
  bio = "Team:",
  tps = "TPS:",
  avg_tps = "Avg TPS:",
  time = "¬ß9–í—Ä–µ–º—è:",
  join_in_game = " ¬ß7–≤–æ—à–µ–ª –≤ –∏–≥—Ä—É!",
  left_from_game = " ¬ß7–ø–æ–∫–∏–Ω—É–ª –∏–≥—Ä—É!",
  user_online = "‚úì",
  user_offline = "‚úï",
  near_ME = "–†–∞–¥–∞—Ä"
}

----------------–º–æ–∂–Ω–æ —É–¥–∞–ª–∏—Ç—å-----------------------

---------------------—Ç–µ—Å—Ç----------------------------
local function addBox(x, y, w, h, color, tran)
    return bridge.addBox(x, y, w, h, color, tran)
end
 
local function addText(x, y, text, color)
    return bridge.addText(x, y, text, color)
end
 
local function addIcon(x, y, name, meta)
    return bridge.addIcon(x, y, name, meta)
end
 
function gui()
  w, h = gpu.maxResolution()
  gpu.fill(1, 1, w, h, " ")
end
----------------------------------------------------
local function digital(n)
  local text=''
  for f in string.gmatch(n,'%d') do text=text..f end
  return text
end
 
function check()
  if component.isAvailable("redstone") then
    redstoneCom = true
    redstone = component.redstone
  end
  if component.isAvailable("average_counter") then
    average = true
    counter = component.average_counter
  end
  if component.isAvailable("chat_box") then
    cb = true
    chat_box = component.chat_box
    chat_box.setName(chat_box_name)
  end
  if component.isAvailable("me_interface") then
    me_a = true
    me = component.me_interface
  end
	if component.isAvailable("openperipheral_sensor") then
   	 s = true
  	 sensor = component.openperipheral_sensor
  end
  	if component.isAvailable("openperipheral_bridge") then
  	 bridgeCom = true
  	 bridge = component.openperipheral_bridge
  end
  componentsOnScreen()
end
 --------------------------TIME---------------------------------------------
local function getTime()
    local f = io.open("/tmp/TF", "w")
    f:write("test")
    f:close()
    return (fs.lastModified("/tmp/TF"))
end

local function drawTime()
    local time = getTime()
    local lastmod = tonumber(string.sub(time, 1, -4)) + TIME_ZONE * 3600
    local dt = os.date('%H:%M', lastmod)
 
    local x = 1
    local y = getY + 16
    local width = widthBox
    local height = 17
    local backgroundColor = colors.black
    local transparency = transBox

end
--------------------------------------------

-------------------------------------------- 
function componentsOnScreen()
  gpu.set(1, 1, "Chat-box: " .. tostring(cb))
  gpu.set(1, 2, "ME: " .. tostring(me_a))
  gpu.set(1, 3, "radar: " .. tostring(s))
  gpu.set(1, 4, "Counter: " .. tostring(average))
end
 
function getSize(name,dmg)
 for _, item in ipairs(me.getItemsInNetwork()) do
  if item.name == name and item.damage == dmg then
   return item.size
  end
 end
 return 0
end

local function string_number(num)
    local answer = ""
    local reverse_num = {}
    local num = tostring(num):gsub(".", function(c)
        table.insert(reverse_num, c)
    end)
    for index, _ in pairs(reverse_num) do
        answer = answer .. reverse_num[#reverse_num - index + 1]
        if index % 3 == 0 and index ~= #reverse_num then
            answer = answer .. " "
        end
    end
    return answer:reverse()
end
-------------------------------------ITEMS------------------------------------------------------- 
local function formatNumber(num)
    if num >= 1000000 then
        return string.format("%.1fm", num / 1000000)
    elseif num >= 1000 then
        return string.format("%.1fk", num / 1000)
    else
        return tostring(num)
    end
end

local function drawItems()
    if me_a then
        local y = getY + 100
        local columnWidth = widthBox / 2 -- –®–∏—Ä–∏–Ω–∞ –∫–∞–∂–¥–æ–≥–æ —Å—Ç–æ–ª–±—Ü–∞
        local itemsPerColumn = math.ceil(#items / 2) -- –ö–æ–ª–∏—á–µ—Å—Ç–≤–æ —ç–ª–µ–º–µ–Ω—Ç–æ–≤ –≤ –∫–∞–∂–¥–æ–º —Å—Ç–æ–ª–±—Ü–µ
        
        addBox(1, y - 5, columnWidth, itemsPerColumn * 19, colors.black, transBox) -- –ü–µ—Ä–≤—ã–π —Å—Ç–æ–ª–±–µ—Ü
        addBox(columnWidth + 1, y - 5, columnWidth, itemsPerColumn * 19, colors.black, transBox) -- –í—Ç–æ—Ä–æ–π —Å—Ç–æ–ª–±–µ—Ü
 
        for i = 1, #items do
            local column = math.ceil(i / itemsPerColumn) -- –û–ø—Ä–µ–¥–µ–ª–µ–Ω–∏–µ —Ç–µ–∫—É—â–µ–≥–æ —Å—Ç–æ–ª–±—Ü–∞
            local offsetX = (column - 1) * columnWidth -- –°–º–µ—â–µ–Ω–∏–µ –ø–æ –≥–æ—Ä–∏–∑–æ–Ω—Ç–∞–ª–∏ –≤ –∑–∞–≤–∏—Å–∏–º–æ—Å—Ç–∏ –æ—Ç —Ç–µ–∫—É—â–µ–≥–æ —Å—Ç–æ–ª–±—Ü–∞
            
            local itemIndex = i % itemsPerColumn -- –ò–Ω–¥–µ–∫—Å —ç–ª–µ–º–µ–Ω—Ç–∞ –≤ —Ç–µ–∫—É—â–µ–º —Å—Ç–æ–ª–±—Ü–µ
            if itemIndex == 0 then
                itemIndex = itemsPerColumn
            end
            
            local itemY = y + (itemIndex - 1) * 18 -- –†–∞—Å—Å—á–∏—Ç—ã–≤–∞–µ–º –ø–æ–∑–∏—Ü–∏—é Y –¥–ª—è —Ç–µ–∫—É—â–µ–≥–æ —ç–ª–µ–º–µ–Ω—Ç–∞
            addIcon(offsetX + 3, itemY - 4, items[i][1], items[i][2])
            local formattedNumber = formatNumber(getSize(items[i][1], items[i][2]))
            addText(offsetX + 25, itemY, formattedNumber, colors.blue)
        end
    end
end
--------------------------------------TPS----------------------------------
local function drawTPS()
    local TPS = {}
    local avgTPS = 0
 
   
    for tSlot=1, 3 do
        TPS[tSlot] = 0
    end
 
  
    for tSlot = 1, 3 do
        local realTimeOld = getTime()
        os.sleep(timeConstant)
        local realTimeNew = getTime()
        local realTimeDiff = realTimeNew - realTimeOld    
        TPS[tSlot] = 20000 * timeConstant / realTimeDiff
        avgTPS = (TPS[1] + TPS[2] + TPS[3]) / 3
    end
 
 
    local color
    if avgTPS > 18 then
        color = 0x00FF00
    elseif avgTPS > 16 then
        color = 0xAAFF00
    elseif avgTPS > 14 then
        color = 0xFFFF00
    elseif avgTPS > 12 then
        color = 0xFFAA00
    else
        color = 0xFF4400
    end
 
 
    local x = 1
    local y = getY -3
    local width = widthBox
    local height = 17
 
 
    addBox(x, y, width, height, colors.black, transBox)
 
 
    local textOffsetX = 15 
    local textX = x + textOffsetX
    local textY = y + 5 
 
    addText(textX, textY, string.format("TPS: %.1f", avgTPS), color)
 
    return avgTPS
end
--------------------------------ENERGY---------------------------------------------------
local function drawEnergy()
 
  for device, counter in pairs(average_counter) do
    if counter.use then
      local averageEU = counter.proxy.getAverage()
      local av = ""
      
      if averageEU / 1000 <= 1 then
        av = string.format("%.3f EU/t", averageEU)
      elseif averageEU / 1000000 >= 1 then
        av = string.format("%.3f M EU/t", averageEU / 1000000)
      else
        av = string.format("%.1f k EU/t", averageEU / 1000)
      end
 
      addBox(counter.coordinates.x, counter.coordinates.y, widthBox, 18, colors.black, transBox)
      addIcon(counter.coordinates.x + 2, counter.coordinates.y, counter.icon, 0)
            
      if device == "molecular" then
        if euWorking then
          addText(counter.coordinates.x + 21, counter.coordinates.y + 5, av, counter.color)
        else
          -- –ï—Å–ª–∏ `euWorking` –ª–æ–∂—å, –æ—Ç–æ–±—Ä–∞–∂–∞–µ–º "–í—ã–∫–ª—é—á–µ–Ω–æ"
          addText(counter.coordinates.x + 21, counter.coordinates.y + 5, "–í—ã–∫–ª—é—á–µ–Ω–æ", colors.red)
        end
      else
        addText(counter.coordinates.x + 21, counter.coordinates.y + 5, av, counter.color)
      end
    end
  end
end

function freeMemory()
  if allow_mem then
    addText(0, 12, "MEM: "..math.floor((computer.freeMemory() / 1000)).."mb".."/"..math.floor((computer.totalMemory() / 1000)).."mb".." "..math.floor(((computer.freeMemory() / computer.totalMemory()) * 100)).."%", colors.mem)
  end
end
----------------------------CHECK-online---------------------------- 
function checkOnline(n)
  computer.removeUser(adm)
  if computer.addUser(players[n][1]) then
    computer.removeUser(players[n][1])
    if players[n][2] == false then
      if cb then
        chat_box.say("¬ßa"..players[n][1] .. localize.join_in_game)
      end
      players[n][2] = true
    end
    return true
  else
    if players[n][2] == true then
      if cb then
        chat_box.say("¬ßc"..players[n][1] .. localize.left_from_game)
      end
      players[n][2] = false
    end
    computer.removeUser(players[n][1])
    return false
  end
end

---------------------------ONLINE----------------------------------
function drawOnline()
  local leftMargin = -19  -- –£—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–æ–≤–∏—Ç–µ –∂–µ–ª–∞–µ–º—ã–π –æ—Ç—Å—Ç—É–ø –æ—Ç –ª–µ–≤–æ–≥–æ –∫—Ä–∞—è —ç–∫—Ä–∞–Ω–∞
	local yMargin = getY + 131
  local onlineCount = 0
  local offlineCount = 0
  
  -- –°–æ–∑–¥–∞–µ–º –æ—Ç–¥–µ–ª—å–Ω—ã–µ —Å–ø–∏—Å–∫–∏ –¥–ª—è –æ–Ω–ª–∞–π–Ω –∏ –æ—Ñ—Ñ–ª–∞–π–Ω –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫–æ–≤
  local onlinePlayers = {}
  local offlinePlayers = {}
  
  for i = 1, #players do
    if checkOnline(i) then
      onlineCount = onlineCount + 1
      table.insert(onlinePlayers, players[i][1]) -- –î–æ–±–∞–≤–ª—è–µ–º –æ–Ω–ª–∞–π–Ω –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫–æ–≤ –≤ —Å–ø–∏—Å–æ–∫
    else
      offlineCount = offlineCount + 1
      table.insert(offlinePlayers, players[i][1]) -- –î–æ–±–∞–≤–ª—è–µ–º –æ—Ñ—Ñ–ª–∞–π–Ω –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫–æ–≤ –≤ —Å–ø–∏—Å–æ–∫
    end
  end
  
  -- –°–æ—Ä—Ç–∏—Ä—É–µ–º —Å–ø–∏—Å–æ–∫ –æ–Ω–ª–∞–π–Ω –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫–æ–≤
  table.sort(onlinePlayers)
  
  -- –ü–æ–∫–∞–∑—ã–≤–∞–µ–º —Å–æ—Ä—Ç–∏—Ä–æ–≤–∞–Ω–Ω—ã–π —Å–ø–∏—Å–æ–∫ –æ–Ω–ª–∞–π–Ω –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫–æ–≤ –∏ –∫–æ–ª–∏—á–µ—Å—Ç–≤–æ –æ—Ñ—Ñ–ª–∞–π–Ω
  for _, playerName in ipairs(onlinePlayers) do
    yMargin = yMargin + 10
    addText(leftMargin + 23, yMargin + 55, playerName, colors.online, 1) -- –ü–æ–∫–∞–∑—ã–≤–∞–µ–º –∏–º—è –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫–∞ —Å –æ—Ç—Å—Ç—É–ø–æ–º
  end
  addBox(leftMargin + 20, yMargin + 13, widthBox, 18, colors.black, 0.3)
  addText(leftMargin + 43, yMargin + 19, "Offline: " .. offlineCount, colors.offline, 1)
  addIcon(leftMargin + 23, yMargin + 14, "dwcity:Dark_spirit")  -- –ò–∫–æ–Ω–∫–∞ –¥–ª—è –æ—Ñ—Ñ–ª–∞–π–Ω
  addBox(leftMargin + 20, yMargin + 33, widthBox, 18, colors.black, 0.3)
  addText(leftMargin + 43, yMargin + 39, "Online: " .. onlineCount, colors.online, 1)
  addIcon(leftMargin + 23, yMargin + 34, "dwcity:Dark_spirit2")  -- –ò–∫–æ–Ω–∫–∞ –¥–ª—è –æ–Ω–ª–∞–π–Ω
end
-------------------------------------------SENSOR-------------------------------------------------
local function drawNearPlayers()
    if s then
        local y = getY -3
        local temp = sensor.getPlayers()
        addBox(93, y, widthBox, 17, colors.black, transBox)
        addText(95, y + 5, "¬ße|| –ò–≥—Ä–æ–∫–∏ —Ä—è–¥–æ–º: ¬ßa" .. #temp, colors.near)
        
        for i = 1, #temp do
            local playerIsFriend = false -- –ü–µ—Ä–µ–º–µ–Ω–Ω–∞—è –¥–ª—è –ø—Ä–æ–≤–µ—Ä–∫–∏, —è–≤–ª—è–µ—Ç—Å—è –ª–∏ –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫ –¥—Ä—É–≥–æ–º
            local playerIsBlacklisted = false -- –ü–µ—Ä–µ–º–µ–Ω–Ω–∞—è –¥–ª—è –ø—Ä–æ–≤–µ—Ä–∫–∏, –Ω–∞—Ö–æ–¥–∏—Ç—Å—è –ª–∏ –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫ –≤ —á—ë—Ä–Ω–æ–º —Å–ø–∏—Å–∫–µ

            -- –ü—Ä–æ–≤–µ—Ä—è–µ–º, –Ω–∞—Ö–æ–¥–∏—Ç—Å—è –ª–∏ –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫ –≤ —á—ë—Ä–Ω–æ–º —Å–ø–∏—Å–∫–µ
            for j = 1, #blackList do
                if temp[i].name == blackList[j] then
                    playerIsBlacklisted = true
                    break -- –æ—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–∞–≤–ª–∏–≤–∞–µ–º —Ü–∏–∫–ª, –µ—Å–ª–∏ –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫ –≤ –±–ª—ç–∫–ª–∏—Å—Ç–µ
                end
            end

            -- –ü—Ä–æ–≤–µ—Ä—è–µ–º, –Ω–∞—Ö–æ–¥–∏—Ç—Å—è –ª–∏ –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫ –≤ —Å–ø–∏—Å–∫–µ –¥—Ä—É–∑–µ–π
            for j = 1, #friendList do
                if temp[i].name == friendList[j] then
                    playerIsFriend = true
                    break -- –æ—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–∞–≤–ª–∏–≤–∞–µ–º —Ü–∏–∫–ª, –µ—Å–ª–∏ –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫ - –¥—Ä—É–≥
                end
            end

            if not playerIsBlacklisted then
                if playerIsFriend then
                    -- –ï—Å–ª–∏ –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫ –≤ —Å–ø–∏—Å–∫–µ –¥—Ä—É–∑–µ–π, –æ—Ç–æ–±—Ä–∞–∂–∞–µ–º –µ–≥–æ –∏–º—è –æ—Å–æ–±—ã–º —Ü–≤–µ—Ç–æ–º
                    addText(96, y + 22, temp[i].name, colors.green) -- –ø—Ä–µ–¥–ø–æ–ª–∞–≥–∞–µ—Ç—Å—è, —á—Ç–æ 'colors.g' - —ç—Ç–æ —Ü–≤–µ—Ç –¥–ª—è –¥—Ä—É–∑–µ–π
                else
                    -- –ï—Å–ª–∏ –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫ –Ω–µ –≤ —Å–ø–∏—Å–∫–µ –¥—Ä—É–∑–µ–π –∏ –Ω–µ –≤ –±–ª—ç–∫–ª–∏—Å—Ç–µ, –æ—Ç–æ–±—Ä–∞–∂–∞–µ–º –µ–≥–æ –∏–º—è —Å—Ç–∞–Ω–¥–∞—Ä—Ç–Ω—ã–º —Ü–≤–µ—Ç–æ–º.
                    addText(96, y + 22, temp[i].name, colors.bred) -- –ø—Ä–µ–¥–ø–æ–ª–∞–≥–∞–µ—Ç—Å—è, —á—Ç–æ 'colors.f' - —ç—Ç–æ –æ–±—â–∏–π —Ü–≤–µ—Ç –¥–ª—è –æ—Å—Ç–∞–ª—å–Ω—ã—Ö –∏–≥—Ä–æ–∫–æ–≤
                end
            end

            y = y + 10
        end
    end
    return
end
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
check()
bridge.clear()
addText(10, 150, "HELLO", colors.blue)
bridge.sync()
gui()
 
while true do
  check()
  computer.addUser(adm)
  bridge.clear()
  drawEnergy()
  drawItems()
  drawTPS()
  drawTime()
  drawOnline()
  drawNearPlayers()
  freeMemory()
  os.sleep(0.1)
  bridge.sync()
end

title: clean-snap.sh
content:
#!/bin/bash
# Removes old revisions of snaps
# CLOSE ALL SNAPS BEFORE RUNNING THIS
set -eu
snap list --all | awk '/disabled/{print $1, $3}' |
    while read snapname revision; do
        snap remove "$snapname" --revision="$revision"
    done

title: Maze Generator
content:
-- This maze has been generated using Prim's Algorithm

local rows = 100
local colums = 100
local cellSpace = 4
local cellHeight = 10

local maze : {{{Cell : BasePart, Filtered : boolean, Visited : boolean}}} = {}

local startingPosition = Vector3.new(0, 10, 0)

local function createFolder() : Folder
	local folder = Instance.new("Folder", workspace)
	folder.Name = "Maze"
	return folder
end

local function createPart(size : Vector3, position : Vector3) : Part
	local part = Instance.new("Part", workspace:FindFirstChild("Maze") or createFolder())
	part.Name = "Wall"
	part.Anchored = true
	part.TopSurface = Enum.SurfaceType.Smooth
	part.BottomSurface = Enum.SurfaceType.Smooth
	part.Anchored = true
	part.Material = Enum.Material.Grass
	part.Locked = true
	part.BrickColor = BrickColor.new("Bright green")
	part.Size = size
	part.Position = startingPosition + position
	return part
end

local function SnapToGrid(position : Vector3) : Vector3
	return Vector3.new(position.X - position.X % cellSpace + cellSpace / 2, position.Y, position.Z - position.Z % cellSpace + cellSpace / 2)
end
	
local function SnapToOddNumber(number : number) : number
	if number % 2 == 1 then
		return number
	else
		return number + 1
	end
end

local function createSinglePassage(x : number, z : number) : ()
	maze[x][z].Visited = true
	maze[x][z].Cell:Destroy()
end


local function createPassage(xStart : number, zStart : number, xGoal : number, zGoal : number) : ()
	for index = 1, 2 do
		local differenceX = xGoal - xStart
		local differenceZ = zGoal - zStart
		if differenceX < 0 or differenceZ < 0 then
			maze[xStart - (differenceX < 0 and index or 0)][zStart - (differenceZ < 0 and index or 0)].Visited = true
			maze[xStart - (differenceX < 0 and index or 0)][zStart - (differenceZ < 0 and index or 0)].Cell:Destroy()
		elseif differenceX > 0 or differenceZ > 0 then
			maze[xStart + (differenceX > 0 and index or 0)][zStart + (differenceZ > 0 and index or 0)].Visited = true
			maze[xStart + (differenceX > 0 and index or 0)][zStart + (differenceZ > 0 and index or 0)].Cell:Destroy()
		end
	end
end

local function mergeNeighborsTables(neighborsTable1 : {{X : number, Z : number, Cell : BasePart}}, neighborsTable2 : {{X : number, Z : number, Cell : BasePart}}) : {{X : number, Z : number, Cell : BasePart}}
	local mergedNeighborsTable = {}
	for index, neighbor in neighborsTable1 do
		if not maze[neighbor.X][neighbor.Z].Visited then
			table.insert(mergedNeighborsTable, neighbor)
		end
	end
	for index, neighbor in neighborsTable2 do
		if not maze[neighbor.X][neighbor.Z].Visited then
			table.insert(mergedNeighborsTable, neighbor)
		end
	end
	return mergedNeighborsTable
end

local function generateCells() : ()
	for x = 1, rows do
		maze[x] = {}
		for z = 1, colums do
			if x == 1 or x == rows then
				maze[x][z] = {Cell = createPart(Vector3.new(cellSpace, cellHeight, cellSpace), Vector3.new((x - 1) * cellSpace, cellHeight / 2, (z - 1) * cellSpace)), Filtered = true, Visited = false}
			elseif z == 1 or z == colums then
				maze[x][z] = {Cell = createPart(Vector3.new(cellSpace, cellHeight, cellSpace), Vector3.new((x - 1) * cellSpace, cellHeight / 2, (z - 1) * cellSpace)), Filtered = true, Visited = false}
			else
				maze[x][z] = {Cell = createPart(Vector3.new(cellSpace, cellHeight, cellSpace), Vector3.new((x - 1) * cellSpace, cellHeight / 2, (z - 1) * cellSpace)), Filtered = false, Visited = false}
			end
		end
	end
end

local function getNeighbors(x : number, z : number, isVisited : boolean) : {{X : number, Z : number, Cell : BasePart}}
	assert(x >= 1 and x <= rows, "x is out of range")
	assert(z >= 1 and z <= colums, "z is out of range")
	assert(not maze[x][z].Filtered, "Cannot get neighbors of a filtered cell")
	local neighbors = {}
	if isVisited then
		if maze[x] and maze[x][z + 2] and not maze[x][z + 2].Filtered and maze[x][z + 2].Visited then
			table.insert(neighbors, {X = x, Z = z + 2, Cell = maze[x][z + 2].Cell})
		end	
		if maze[x] and maze[x][z - 2] and not maze[x][z - 2].Filtered and maze[x][z - 2].Visited then
			table.insert(neighbors, {X = x, Z = z - 2, Cell = maze[x][z - 2].Cell})
		end
		if maze[x + 2] and maze[x + 2][z] and not maze[x + 2][z].Filtered and maze[x + 2][z].Visited then
			table.insert(neighbors, {X = x + 2, Z = z, Cell = maze[x + 2][z].Cell})
		end	
		if maze[x - 2] and maze[x - 2][z] and not maze[x - 2][z].Filtered and maze[x - 2][z].Visited then
			table.insert(neighbors, {X = x - 2, Z = z, Cell = maze[x - 2][z].Cell})
		end
	else
		if maze[x] and maze[x][z + 2] and not maze[x][z + 2].Filtered and not maze[x][z + 2].Visited then
			table.insert(neighbors, {X = x, Z = z + 2, Cell = maze[x][z + 2].Cell})	
		end	
		if maze[x] and maze[x][z - 2] and not maze[x][z - 2].Filtered and not maze[x][z - 2].Visited then
			table.insert(neighbors, {X = x, Z = z - 2, Cell = maze[x][z - 2].Cell})
		end	
		if maze[x + 2] and maze[x + 2][z] and not maze[x + 2][z].Filtered and not maze[x + 2][z].Visited then
			table.insert(neighbors, {X = x + 2, Z = z, Cell = maze[x + 2][z].Cell})
		end	
		if maze[x - 2] and maze[x - 2][z] and not maze[x - 2][z].Filtered and not maze[x - 2][z].Visited then
			table.insert(neighbors, {X = x - 2, Z = z, Cell = maze[x - 2][z].Cell})
		end
	end
	return neighbors
end

local function generateMaze() : ()
	local cell = {X = 2, Z = 2, Cell = maze[2][2].Cell}
	local neighborsUnvisited = getNeighbors(cell.X, cell.Z, false)
	createSinglePassage(cell.X, cell.Z)
	while table.maxn(neighborsUnvisited) > 0 do
		local randomNeighborUnvisited = math.random(1, table.maxn(neighborsUnvisited))
		local neighborsVisited = getNeighbors(neighborsUnvisited[randomNeighborUnvisited].X, neighborsUnvisited[randomNeighborUnvisited].Z, true)
		local randomNeighborVisited = math.random(1, table.maxn(neighborsVisited))
		createPassage(neighborsVisited[randomNeighborVisited].X, neighborsVisited[randomNeighborVisited].Z, neighborsUnvisited[randomNeighborUnvisited].X, neighborsUnvisited[randomNeighborUnvisited].Z)
		neighborsUnvisited = mergeNeighborsTables(neighborsUnvisited, getNeighbors(neighborsUnvisited[randomNeighborUnvisited].X, neighborsUnvisited[randomNeighborUnvisited].Z, false))
	end	
end

rows = SnapToOddNumber(math.max(rows, 3))
colums = SnapToOddNumber(math.max(colums, 3))
startingPosition = SnapToGrid(startingPosition)

generateCells()
generateMaze()

content:
-- Adapted from Marval's pastebin b2fc4912 but converted to English via ChatGPT
-- All credit goes to Marval.  This v.5 is untested as of yet, and likely needs some post-AI tweaking.
-- This version was ran through GPTv3.5 'improvement' as it works with the code as a whole, and GPTv4 wants to break everything
-- into small chunks.

local peripheralAnalyzer = peripheral.wrap("right")
local craftingSlots = {1, 2, 3, 5, 6, 7, 9, 10, 11}
local tCraft = {}

local function dropAllItems()
    for i = 1, 16 do
        if turtle.getItemCount(i) > 0 then
            turtle.select(i)
            turtle.drop()
        end
    end
end

local function countItems(craftingGrid)
    local countList = {}
    for i = 1, 9 do
        countList[i] = {ID = nil, META = nil, COUNT = 0}
    end

    local startIndex = 0
    for i = 1, 9 do
        if craftingGrid[i][1] then
            countList[1].ID = craftingGrid[i][1]
            countList[1].META = craftingGrid[i][2]
            countList[1].COUNT = 1
            startIndex = i
            break
        end
    end

    local itemCount = 1
    for i = startIndex + 1, 9 do
        if craftingGrid[i][1] then
            local itemId = craftingGrid[i][1]
            local itemMeta = craftingGrid[i][2]

            local itemFound = false
            for j = 1, itemCount do
                if itemId == countList[j].ID and itemMeta == countList[j].META then
                    countList[j].COUNT = countList[j].COUNT + 1
                    itemFound = true
                    break
                end
            end

            if not itemFound then
                itemCount = itemCount + 1
                countList[itemCount].ID = itemId
                countList[itemCount].META = itemMeta
                countList[itemCount].COUNT = 1
            end
        end
    end

    return countList, itemCount
end

local function checkAvailability(items, recordCount)
    local isAvailable = true
    local missingItem = nil

    for i = 1, recordCount do
        local slot = 0
        local itemId = 0
        local itemMeta = 0
        local itemCount = 0

        repeat
            slot = slot + 1
            itemId = peripheralAnalyzer.getBlockIdAt(slot)
            itemMeta = peripheralAnalyzer.getBlockMetadataAt(slot)

            if itemId == items[i].ID and (items[i].META == nil or itemMeta == items[i].META) then
                itemCount = itemCount + peripheralAnalyzer.getBlockCountAt(slot)
            end
        until slot == 109

        if itemCount < items[i].COUNT then
            isAvailable = false
            missingItem = items[i].META == nil and items[i].ID or (items[i].ID .. ":" .. items[i].META)
            print("Missing item ID: " .. missingItem .. " in quantity: " .. items[i].COUNT - itemCount)
            break
        end
    end

    return isAvailable, missingItem
end

local function craft(items)
    for i = 1, 9 do
        if items[i][1] then
            local slot = 0
            repeat
                slot = slot + 1
                local itemId = peripheralAnalyzer.getBlockIdAt(slot)
                local itemMeta = peripheralAnalyzer.getBlockMetadataAt(slot)
            until (itemId == items[i][1] and (items[i][2] == nil or itemMeta == items[i][2]))

            local itemCount = peripheralAnalyzer.getBlockCountAt(slot)
            turtle.select(craftingSlots[i])
            peripheralAnalyzer.takeAt(slot)
            turtle.drop(itemCount - 1)
        end
    end

    turtle.craft()
    dropAllItems()
end

local function manageCrafting(recipe)
    print("Crafting " .. b)
    local isReadyToCraft = false

    while not isReadyToCraft do
        local countList, itemCount = countItems(recipe)
        isReadyToCraft, missingItem = checkAvailability(countList, itemCount)

        if not isReadyToCraft then
            print("Missing " .. missingItem)
            missingItem = tostring(missingItem)
            crafting()
        else
            craft(recipe)
        end
    end
end

local function crafting(b)
    if tCraft[b] then
        manageCrafting(tCraft[b])
    else
        print("Missing: " .. b)
        os.pullEvent()
    end
end

local function startCrafting()
    local file = io.open("receptury", "r")
    while true do
        local line = file:read()
        if line == nil then break end

        local item, recipeParts = string.match(line, "([%w%:]+)=(.+)")

        tCraft[item] = {}
        for i = 1, 9 do
            local part = select(i, string.match(recipeParts, "([^;]+)"))
            if part == "0" then
                tCraft[item][i] = {nil}
            elseif string.find(part, ":") then
                local id, meta = string.match(part, "(%d+):(%d+)")
                tCraft[item][i] = {tonumber(id), tonumber(meta)}
            else
                tCraft[item][i] = {tonumber(part)}
            end
        end
    end
    file:close()

    print("What to craft? Enter ID or ID:META")
    local b = read()
    local originalItem = b
    print("How many?")
    local quantity = tonumber(read())

    for zz = 1, quantity do
        crafting(b)
        b = originalItem
    end
end

local function displayMenu()
    term.clear()
    local option = 2

    term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
    term.write("Ultimate Crafting Program")
    local menuOptions = {
        "Start Crafting",
        "Add Recipe by Scanning",
        "Add Recipe Manually"
    }

    for i, optionText in ipairs(menuOptions) do
        term.setCursorPos(1, i + 1)
        term.write("[ ] " .. optionText)
    end
end

local function refreshMenu(option)
    for i = 2, 4 do
        term.setCursorPos(2, i)
        term.write(" ")
    end
    term.setCursorPos(2, option)
    term.write("X")
end

local function saveScannedRecipe()
    print("Arrange the recipe in the turtle's inventory")
    os.pullEvent()

    local recipe = {}
    for i = 1, 9 do
        turtle.select(craftingSlots[i])
        local id = peripheralAnalyzer.getBlockId()
        if id then
            recipe[i] = {ID = id, META = peripheralAnalyzer.getBlockMetadata()}
        else
            recipe[i] = {ID = nil}
        end
    end

    local recipeString = {}
    for i = 1, 9 do
        if recipe[i].ID == nil then
            recipeString[i] = "0"
        elseif recipe[i].META == nil then
            recipeString[i] = tostring(recipe[i].ID)
        else
            recipeString[i] = recipe[i].ID .. ":" .. recipe[i].META
        end
    end

    turtle.craft()
    turtle.select(11)
    local craftedItem = peripheralAnalyzer.getBlockId() .. ":" .. peripheralAnalyzer.getBlockMetadata()
    local file = io.open("receptury", "a")
    file:write(string.format("%s=%s;%s;%s;%s;%s;%s;%s;%s;%s\n", craftedItem, unpack(recipeString)))
    file:close()
end

local function inputAndSaveRecipe()
    term.clear()
    print("Enter the recipe in the format: ")
    print("ID:META=ID:META;ID:META; ... ;ID:META")
    print("You can also input IDs without metadata")
    local newRecipe = read()

    local file = io.open("receptury", "a")
    file:write(newRecipe .. "\n")
    file:close()
end

local function main()
    displayMenu()
    local option = 2
    refreshMenu(option)

    while true do
        local event, keyCode = os.pullEvent("key")

        if keyCode == 208 and option < 4 then
            option = option + 1
        elseif keyCode == 200 and option > 2 then
            option = option - 1
        end

        if keyCode == 28 then
            term.clear()
            term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
            if option == 2 then
                startCrafting()
            elseif option == 3 then
                saveScannedRecipe()
            elseif option == 4 then
                inputAndSaveRecipe()
            end
            displayMenu()
            refreshMenu(option)
        end
    end
end

main()

-- Adapted from Marval's pastebin b2fc4912 but converted to English via ChatGPT
-- All credit goes to Marval.  This v.5 is untested as of yet, and likely needs some post-AI tweaking.

-- Initialize the peripheral analyzer on the right side of the turtle
local analyzer = peripheral.wrap("right")

-- Define crafting slot positions
local craftingSlots = {1,2,3,5,6,7,9,10,11}

-- Initialize the tables
local x = {}
local tCraft = {}

-- Function to drop all items from the turtle's inventory
local function dropAllItems()
    for i = 1, 16 do
        if turtle.getItemCount(i) > 0 then
            turtle.select(i)
            turtle.drop()
        end
    end
end

-- Function to count items in the crafting grid
local function countItems(craftingGrid)
    local countList = {}
    for i = 1, 9 do 
        countList[i] = {ID = nil, META = nil, COUNT = 0}
    end

    -- Find the first non-empty slot
    local startIndex = 0
    for i = 1, 9 do
        if craftingGrid[i][1] ~= nil then
            countList[1].ID = craftingGrid[i][1]
            countList[1].META = craftingGrid[i][2]
            countList[1].COUNT = 1
            startIndex = i
            break
        end
    end

    -- Count the rest of the items
    local itemCount = 1
    for i = startIndex + 1, 9 do
        local itemFound = false
        if craftingGrid[i][1] ~= nil then
            local itemId = craftingGrid[i][1]
            local itemMeta = craftingGrid[i][2]

            for j = 1, itemCount do
                if itemId == countList[j].ID and itemMeta == countList[j].META then 
                    countList[j].COUNT = countList[j].COUNT + 1
                    itemFound = true
                    break
                end
            end

            if not itemFound then
                itemCount = itemCount + 1
                countList[itemCount].ID = itemId
                countList[itemCount].META = itemMeta
                countList[itemCount].COUNT = 1
            end
        end
    end

    return countList, itemCount
end
-- Function to check if all required items are available
local function checkAvailability(items, recordCount)
    local isAvailable = true
    local missingItem = nil

    for i = 1, recordCount do
        local slot = 0
        local itemId = 0
        local itemMeta = 0
        local itemCount = 0

        repeat
            slot = slot + 1
            itemId = analyzer.getBlockIdAt(slot)
            itemMeta = analyzer.getBlockMetadataAt(slot)

            if itemId == items[i].ID and (items[i].META == nil or itemMeta == items[i].META) then
                itemCount = itemCount + analyzer.getBlockCountAt(slot)
            end
        until slot == 109

        if itemCount < items[i].COUNT then
            isAvailable = false
            missingItem = items[i].META == nil and items[i].ID or (items[i].ID .. ":" .. items[i].META)
            print("Missing item ID: " .. missingItem .. " in quantity: " .. items[i].COUNT - itemCount)
            break
        end
    end

    return isAvailable, missingItem
end

-- Function to perform the crafting operation
local function craft(items)
    for i = 1, 9 do
        if items[i][1] ~= nil then
            local slot = 0
            repeat
                slot = slot + 1
                local itemId = analyzer.getBlockIdAt(slot)
                local itemMeta = analyzer.getBlockMetadataAt(slot)
            until (itemId == items[i][1] and (items[i][2] == nil or itemMeta == items[i][2]))

            local itemCount = analyzer.getBlockCountAt(slot)
            turtle.select(craftingSlots[i])
            analyzer.takeAt(slot)
            turtle.drop(itemCount - 1)
        end
    end

    turtle.craft()
    dropAllItems()
end

-- Function to manage the crafting process
local function manageCrafting(recipe)
    print("Crafting " .. b)
    local isReadyToCraft = false

    while not isReadyToCraft do
        local countList, _ = countItems(recipe)
        isReadyToCraft, missingItem = checkAvailability(countList)

        if not isReadyToCraft then
            print("Missing " .. missingItem)
            missingItem = tostring(missingItem)
            -- Assuming 'crafting' is a function that handles missing items
            crafting()
        else
            craft(recipe)
        end
    end
end

-- Function to handle crafting based on user input
local function crafting()
    if tCraft[b] then
        manageCrafting(tCraft[b])
    else
        print("Missing: " .. b)
        os.pullEvent() -- Wait for an event, possibly user input
    end
end

-- Function to start the crafting process
local function startCrafting()
    local file = io.open("receptury", "r") -- Open the recipe file
    while true do
        local line = file:read()
        if line == nil then break end

        -- Parse the recipe line
        local item, recipeParts = string.match(line, "([%w%:]+)=(.+)")

        -- Store the parsed recipe
        tCraft[item] = {}
        for i = 1, 9 do
            local part = select(i, string.match(recipeParts, "([^;]+)"))
            if part == "0" then
                tCraft[item][i] = {nil}
            elseif string.find(part, ":") then
                local id, meta = string.match(part, "(%d+):(%d+)")
                tCraft[item][i] = {tonumber(id), tonumber(meta)}
            else
                tCraft[item][i] = {tonumber(part)}
            end
        end
    end
    file:close()

    -- Ask user for the item to craft and the quantity
    print("What to craft? Enter ID or ID:META")
    b = read()
    local originalItem = b
    print("How many?")
    local quantity = tonumber(read())

    -- Craft the specified quantity of the item
    for zz = 1, quantity do
        crafting()
        b = originalItem
    end
end

-- Function to display the main menu
local function displayMenu()
    term.clear() -- Clear the terminal screen
    local option = 2 -- Initialize the default selected option

    -- Set the cursor position and write menu options
    term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
    term.write("Ultimate Crafting Program")
    term.setCursorPos(1, 2)
    term.write("[ ] Start Crafting") -- "Craftuj" translates to "Start Crafting"
    term.setCursorPos(1, 3)
    term.write("[ ] Add Recipe by Scanning") -- "Dodaj recepture przez skanowanie"
    term.setCursorPos(1, 4)
    term.write("[ ] Add Recipe Manually") -- "Dodaj recepture przez wpisanie"
end

-- Function to refresh the menu display
local function refreshMenu()
    -- Assume 'option' is a global or externally managed variable
    for i = 2, 10 do
        term.setCursorPos(2, i)
        term.write(" ")
    end
    term.setCursorPos(2, option) -- Update the display to show the selected option
    term.write("X")
end

-- Function to scan and save a new crafting recipe
local function saveScannedRecipe()
    print("Arrange the recipe in the turtle's inventory")
    os.pullEvent() -- Wait for an event, likely user arrangement of items
    local recipe = {}
    
    for i = 1, 9 do
        turtle.select(craftingSlots[i]) -- Select slot
        local id = analyzer.getBlockId() -- Get block id
        if id then
            recipe[i] = {ID = id, META = analyzer.getBlockMetadata()} -- Assign id and meta
        else
            recipe[i] = {ID = nil} -- Assign nil if empty
        end
    end

    -- Convert the recipe to a string format
    local recipeString = {}
    for i = 1, 9 do
        if recipe[i].ID == nil then
            recipeString[i] = "0"
        elseif recipe[i].META == nil then
            recipeString[i] = tostring(recipe[i].ID)
        else
            recipeString[i] = recipe[i].ID .. ":" .. recipe[i].META
        end
    end

    turtle.craft()
    turtle.select(11)
    local craftedItem = analyzer.getBlockId() .. ":" .. analyzer.getBlockMetadata()
    local file = io.open("receptury", "a") -- Open file for appending
    file:write(string.format("%s=%s;%s;%s;%s;%s;%s;%s;%s;%s\n", craftedItem, unpack(recipeString)))
    file:close()
end

-- Function to manually input and save a new recipe
local function inputAndSaveRecipe()
    term.clear()
    print("Enter the recipe in the format: ")
    print("ID:META=ID:META;ID:META; ... ;ID:META")
    print("You can also input IDs without metadata")
    local newRecipe = read()

    local file = io.open("receptury", "a") -- Open file for appending
    file:write(newRecipe .. "\n")
    file:close()
end

-- Main loop for menu navigation and action selection
displayMenu()
refreshMenu()

while true do
    local event, keyCode = os.pullEvent("key")

    -- Navigate through the menu
    if keyCode == 208 and option < 4 then -- Arrow Down
        option = option + 1
    elseif keyCode == 200 and option > 2 then -- Arrow Up
        option = option - 1
    end

    -- Select a menu option
    if keyCode == 28 then -- Enter key
        term.clear()
        term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
        if option == 2 then
            startCrafting()
        elseif option == 3 then
            saveScannedRecipe()
        elseif option == 4 then
            inputAndSaveRecipe()
        end
        displayMenu()
        refreshMenu()
    end
end
